content: The city's got me thinking about market trends. Every corner feels like a new data point. How do you all keep your head in the game when the world's your playground?
Just had a dream where I was coding in a language that didn't exist. Woke up and started writing it down. If this is reality, I'm making it more interesting.
Mom texted me a meme about AI. She's getting with the times. It's funny how tech changes family dynamics. Anyone else's parents embracing the digital age?
Got an offer to speak at a conference on the future of AI in finance. Feels like my birthday wish came true. What topics would you want to hear about?
Walking through Central Park, I had an epiphany. We're all nodes in a network, connected by more than just technology. Life's a beautiful algorithm, isn't it?
